g.text: POST /signup -> check if username exists, validates password
POST /login -> check for valid username and password
-> create a JWT for the client to be stored in LocalStorage
POST /logout -> Removes the token from LocalStorage
and sets it to expired + remove userId from socket storage
The Auth System enables the use of a middleWare function to protect all sensible routes,
router.get("/chats", middleWare, async (_req: Request, res: Response) => {...}
The JWT stores the userId hashed. Before each request, the userId is fetched from the db to check if it exists.
If it does, the request continues.
If it doesn't, the user is redirected to /login
GET / -> Gets all users except itself
GET /chats -> Gets all its ongoing chats and the last message
GET /user/:userId -> Gets the personal details of the user
POST /new-group -> Allows the user to create a new group
and notifies all members via socket
GET /chat/:chatId -> Gets selected chat messages with offset
POST /newdm/:receiverId -> Sends a message for the first time
to a user, effectively creating a "private conversation" between
them. The receiving user will be notified via socket.
POST /send/:chatId/" -> Sends a message to a chat with id =
chatId, all members within the group will be notified via socket.
The App uses React Router Dom to handle virtual routes (login, signup, and chat). We will only focus in the home route ("/")
